        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.40"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">40</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MILDRED R. BENNETT</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    329 North Cedar 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">RED CLOUD, NEBRASKA</hi> 68970 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 26, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine St.</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Neb. 68505</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Last weekend I was in Kearney to give a talk to Sigma Tau Delta and of course I saw Stan and had a beer with him. We talked mostly of you and how we hoped you were out of the hospital and able to keep your lecture appointments. From what I've heard you've got a lot of them to do.</p>
                
                <p>I received an invitation to come to one April 16 in Lincoln at St. Paul's church, I think, but that was the day after our spring conference and we always have committee meetings and lef<del/><add>t</add> overs to talk about.</p>
                
                <p>One of our speakers at the conference was a girl from India who is a Zoroasterian, but who seems also to believe in reincarnation. She gave me the name of another writerwho<sic>writer who</sic> is doing some good things, so I have sent for a list of the books and will see what good things I can find.</p>
                
                <p>She thought that Lobsang Rampa , the mystic I wrote about before, is still alive in Tibet. He has many more books that I want to read, but haven't been able to get yet.</p>
                
                <p>I saw a copy of the new <hi rend="caps">BLACK ELK SPEAKS</hi> and it looked very attractive. I hope it is selling well. I hope you take your books with you when you talk as people always want autographed copies.</p>
                
                <p>When I was in Kearney, I heard John Ciardi talk and not a bookstore and his booksfor<sic>books for</sic> sale. I thought it was a shame.</p>
                
                <p>I have two more talks to give this weekend and then a little talk the 15th of May and that ends all the speeches I have to make this spring. We plan to go to Estes Park for a medical meeting in June. I hope <del>r</del><add>t</add>hat will be fun.</p> 
                
                <p>Take care of yourself and don't go out on a rainy day like today.</p>
                
                <p>Affectionate thoughts from all of us here and especially from Alicia.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <signed>Mildred</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
                
                
